BE CAREFUL! 

The commands from page 7:

Listing 9. Deploy an application to be used to connect to another pod
  [student@workstation ~]$  oc create deploy hello-php --image registry.ocp4.example.com:8443/redhattraining/php-hello-dockerfile
Listing 10. Deploy an application to be used to access the previous hello world app
  [student@workstation ~]$  oc create deploy hello-nginx --image registry.ocp4.example.com:8443/redhattraining/hello-world-nginx

ARE ACTUALLY:

Listing 9. Deploy an application to be used to connect to another pod
  [student@workstation ~]$  oc create deploy hello-php --image quay.io/redhattraining/php-hello-dockerfile
Listing 10. Deploy an application to be used to access the previous hello world app
  [student@workstation ~]$  oc create deploy hello-nginx --image quay.io/redhattraining/hello-world-nginx




To download Butane CLI: (Converts files defined in the format presented here (https://github.com/coreos/butane/blob/main/docs/config-openshift-v4_13.md) into a machine config)
https://mirror.openshift.com/pub/openshift-v4/clients/butane/latest/

Remember that you need to define a machine config pool as stated here:
https://www.redhat.com/en/blog/openshift-container-platform-4-how-does-machine-config-pool-work
